25/10/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Missing Persons Institute announced on Friday (October 23rd) that a new mass grave with remnants of at least 19 victims of the 1995 Srebrenica massacre was found in a 30m-deep vertical cave near Tuzla.
Some of the victims had their hands tied and eyes covered with bands.
Nearly 8,000 Bosnian Muslims are believed to have been killed but around 5,600 victims have been identified in 70 mass graves around Srebrenica.
(AFP, MIA - 23/10/09)
